\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {1}{\ignorespaces Schematic overview of CAPO. (a) Within-trajectory token dependence induces nontrivial covariance structure in trajectory gradients, which can amplify gradient variance as a function of response length. (b) CAPO reweights trajectories by learned posterior precisions (length and covariance-aware) to obtain an unbiased, lower-variance aggregate update.\relax }}{3}{figure.caption.1}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {2}{\ignorespaces CAPO Model: Horizontal layout with enlarged plates and unified \scriptsize labeling.\relax }}{4}{figure.caption.2}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {3}{\ignorespaces Training dynamics (validation Avg@8 vs. global step) for a representative subset of methods.\relax }}{45}{figure.caption.15}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {4}{\ignorespaces Stability summary. Each point corresponds to a method, plotted by monotonicity (higher is better) and negative drift rate (lower is better).\relax }}{46}{figure.caption.17}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {5}{\ignorespaces Verifier success by response-length decile. This analysis highlights whether a method disproportionately favors short (or long) trajectories even when end-to-end accuracy is similar.\relax }}{47}{figure.caption.18}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {6}{\ignorespaces Synthetic covariance benchmark: normalized mean-squared scalar advantage versus trajectory length. Each panel corresponds to a covariance regime; within a panel, curves show $\mathbb {E}[A^2\mid L]/\mathbb {E}[A^2\mid L_{\min }]$ for the advantages produced by GRPO, $\Delta L$ baselines, and CAPO variants. Curves above $1$ indicate length amplification (long trajectories receive disproportionately high-variance learning signals), while curves below $1$ indicate suppression of long trajectories.\relax }}{48}{figure.caption.19}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {7}{\ignorespaces Synthetic covariance benchmark: signal allocation across length bins. For each covariance regime, bars show the fraction of the total squared learning signal $\DOTSB \sum@ \slimits@ _i A_i^2$ contributed by each length bin. This diagnostic complements Figure~\ref {fig:synthetic-covariance} by directly visualizing whether an update concentrates on long trajectories under different dependence structures.\relax }}{49}{figure.caption.20}%
